window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b><i>A new darkness is seeping into Sterling Falls, and I’ve drawn its ire.</i></b><br> <br> When a masked stranger declares he wants our ruin—mine, my brother’s, the whole town’s—I hope he’s bluffing.<br> <br> A series of escalating events later, and it’s clear the threat is very present.</p> <p>It’s not only present, but it drags up old nightmares from my past.<br> <br> To keep my beloved city safe, I need to find this masked man and eliminate the threat.<br> <br> I can’t do it on my own, but the three men poised to help are the ones I am almost certain I can’t trust.<br> <br> <b>Kade Laurent, the elusive and thrilling newcomer</b>, leverages Olympus to get close to me.<br> <br> <b>Reese Avery, a ghost from my past,</b> brings with him the trauma I’ve tried to bury. But he says he’s here to make amends…<br> <br> <b>Saint Hart, the partner of my dead best friend, </b>and I will never get along. Especially since I’ve been tasked with keeping him alive. At least, I <i>was</i> convinced we were going to be mortal enemies forever—until we hate-screw in my kitchen…<br> <br> Now things are all messed up, and I don’t know who I can rely on.<br> <br> <b><i>All I want is peace, but with danger climbing around me, it seems I’m destined for the opposite.</i></b></p>"; 
